-- Kleiner Perkins Raises $525 Million for Web, Clean Tech
-- B y   A r i   L e v y
-- 2012-05-18T02:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-18/kleiner-perkins-raises-525-million-for-web-clean-tech.html
Kleiner Perkins Caufield & Byers, the
venture capitalists that backed Google Inc. and Amazon.com Inc.,
raised $525 million for investments in startups focused on
digital technology, alternative energy and life sciences.  The fund will be led by 10 partners, including  John Doerr 
and  Bing Gordon , the Menlo Park, California-based company said
today in a statement. New partners in the fund include former
Twitter Inc. executive Mike Abbott and clean-tech investors Amol
Deshpande and Wen Hsieh.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ari Levy in San Francisco at 
 alevy5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tom Giles at   tgiles5@bloomberg.net  